reviews.review_text: Review for Hungry Guys in Vancouver Had the pleasure of stumbling upon this cozy Mexican-themed bar & restaurant while shopping around Vancouver on vacation. I was initially drawn in by their enticing drink specials   $3.49 shots including choices like Jose Cuervo tequila, Malibu coconut rum, Fireball cinnamon whiskey, and both red and blue kamikazes. They didnt just win me over with their drink menu; their food options seemed diverse and delectable. I had just finished eating, but I had watched several other patrons, absolutely devour their tacos and burgers, and they look really good!!! The ambiance is warm and welcoming, with rustic countertops, soft seating, and high ceilings that give a spacious feel to the intimate setting. One of the standout features was the partially open kitchen; its always reassuring to see a clean and well-maintained culinary space. I saw staff constantly making aa cleanliness effort. Tayanne was my server for most of the evening, and her friendly demeanour made me feel as if I was catching up with an old friend. Later, Vesa took over, ensuring the service quality remained impeccable. The presence of an attentive manager overseeing operations added an extra layer of professionalism. For solo travellers like myself or anyone for that matter, this spot guarantees comfort and a fantastic dining experience. If youre out shopping at Marshalls, Sephora, or any nearby  luxe  stores and fancy a reasonably priced meal/snack or quick drink, I highly recommend this gem. It s a wonderful place to unwind, whether you choose the bar or a comfy table. Cheers to a memorable experience! Vegetarian options: Veggie burger! Tofu spicy rice bowl! Caesar  salad, avocado taco salad with tofu
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi California, Thank you soooo much for the lovely review. You are amazing!!

reviews.review_text: Popped in for a couple of tacos which were delicious. The server didnt speak Spanish, which is unusual in the Mexican restaurants I know, but she was very attentive and friendly. Nice atmosphere, bar seating or tables.

It s the second time that I go there, Maria is such a beautiful and nice waitress! Friendly staff in general, I tried the nachos, really good cream and avocado, but the beef was a little cold    after all, good bar  to have fun! <3

I wish I could have taken a picture of the vegetarian tacos I ordered cause not only did I go in and order once, I came back the next night to order them again! I know people may say $7 a taco is a lot but for real, IT WAS WORTH IT. I stumbled across this place by chance just walking a couple blocks from my hotel and I was immediately in love. Even though I wasn t able to get a picture of my rapidly consumed food. I managed to get a photo of the inside of the facility. I was absolutely amazed by the lights and the fact all their ceiling plants are real! SO amazed in fact, that I came home and recreated the restaurant vibe in my hallway *also with real plants!* (See photo)
Great place to grab a bite if youre in Downtown. Ordered the Classic burger for the second time. Was really tasteful and mouth watering and beats most corporate restaurants out there!!!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: H Kevin. We really appreciate your honest opinion. You re amazing!

reviews.review_text: The hotdog is very good, it comes with fries   but I wanted to add mushrooms. Next time I will try the spicy burger!

Delicious, fresh food! Great flavours, prices, and options! The staff was super friendly as well! We tried the nachos, bowl, salad, soup, tacos, burrito, cheesecake, and virgin mojitos, everything was great. The atmosphere is very cozy and it s not too busy either. Definitely will come back! (We already came three times during the week we were in Vancouver)

WOW. We stumble upon this eatery when visiting Hornby st for a concert night.  Unreal food. Probably the best burger I had in 10 years. Homemade everything, even down to the sauces.  Highly recommend. Great happy hour as well :)
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much, Todd. You are amazing!!

reviews.review_text: This was our second time coming to Hungry Guys and, it does not disappoint! Amazing food, probably one of the best burgers we had ever had ! Our first visit here we had the tacos and a rice bowl, absolutely amazing !! Great drinks and the best service from friendly staff that truly care. Highly reccomend, I can not rave them enough! We will always come here when we visit from the Island!!!!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Emily, thank you sooooo much for the lovely comments. You are amazing!

reviews.review_text: I got the Spicy Mexican Burrito and a burrito bowl on two separate occasions, and both were delicious. There was plenty of shredded pork with a good balance of veggies and rice. The staff was also very friendly. Would definitely recommend!
Amazing food & service. The burger is legit insane  I m selective with burgers and hughly recommend. Also the rice bowl! Helena was our server and went way above & beyond. Will be back for sure!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Raj, thank you sooo much for the lovely comments. You are amazing!

reviews.review_text: Amazing salads and brunch options.  Had the Avocado Taco Salad. Great portions considering the price and quality. I had take out, but would definitely eat in if I had the time.  Highly recommend.

Came by for a late lunch. Great options for building your own salad or bowl. I added grilled chicken as a protein, and combined with a brown rice base and 4 toppings, it was quite filling. My friend had a bowl and added guacamole, it was tasty and the guac balanced out how spicy their sriracha was! They appear to have seating upstairs, but it was closed when we went. Not a place for large groups as most of the tables are for 2. Service when ordering/customizing the meal was friendly. Will be back if Im in the area!
Great service Delicious food I loved the burrito bowls and nachos. I added some extras to it. I had the chocolate chicken! It was delicious I had to go back for more Food : 5/5 |

It looks like for the past two weeks, people have been rating this place less than two stars. I think the renovations were an improvement and made the restaurant more open and vibrant, but it will take time to get used to. I ordered the chicken burrito bowl, which was delicious! #supportlocals #supportsmallbusiness

So glad we decided to stop by this place while in Vancouver for the weekend. The food was awesome, the chairs were comfy and our server was great! She recommended an alternative sauce (which was soo good) when I asked if the one included contained certain ingredients. Vegetarian options: Vegetarian and Vegan friendly!
The best burrito weve ever had. Delicious food and cocktails. Loved it!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much. You are amazing!

reviews.review_text: Great spot to chill, eat and take in smooth vibes!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much, Kevin. You are amazing!!

reviews.review_text: Great place for happy hour or  brunch. The food is tasty and they have good tequila specials. In the heart of Granville but a really cozy vibe inside. Perfect place for a quick bite or a cozy date. The staff here are wonderful!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much, Heather. You are amazing!

reviews.review_text: Cheap food, good vibes, amazing portions. My fav are the burritos as they are quite good and the drinks arent that bad either and very cheaply priced. Vegetarian options: Not that great in my opinion. The tofu is just cold tofu and no other meat like alternatives

A best place to have brunch or dinner. Very healthy and a good option when you have to eat something light or heavy before that power walk or just a walk around downtown. I took build your salad veggie pick four with a glass or lemonade and tortilla chip makes perfect dinner for me
Get Tacos. Best Ive had in a long time. Every one is amazing, packed full, and larger than you expect for the price in a downtown Vancouver restaurant.
Fantastic portions for cheap! For 68 bucks we got 5 meals that were more than filling and 5 drinks. Would recommend to anyone who is looking for a cheap bite that it fresh and filling in Vancouver!!
The most delicious mexican roll Ive ever ate! Dont be afraid of the name Spicy, It is mild and it taste good
It was lovely, Azumi and Helena were amazing hosts. I love their Ceviche and Fish Tacos but wish they added French fries to their menu. It would be next level experience.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you sooo much for the feedback, Ayesha. I agree. French fries would be nice to be on the menu. Hopefully soon.

reviews.review_text: Hungry guys is always our first stop on a night out- the weekend shot specials are a bargain and the staff are all so incredibly kind. If youre planning for a night on the town definitely make sure this is one of your stops!! Vegetarian options: One of our friends had a fully vegan taco with only minor alterations to the dish!
Everything here is just right. The food is outstanding especially the tacos and the drinks taste of quality. I have been coming here for many years and have always experienced outstanding service.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Marla. Thank you sooo much for the lovely comments. You re amazing!

reviews.review_text: The spicy Mexican burrito was great! It was large  and filling!

Seriously good, fresh food at a very good price! They re exactly like chipotle except much more flavourful, fresher, and environmentally friendly- their utensils are compostable! If I lived here, it would definitely be my go to spot. The place is very aesthetically pleasing and although it doesn t seem like they have a public wifi, the nearby Tim Hortons wifi works well enough.

Amazing atmosphere. This place has a great selection of food for even the pickiest of eaters. Its set up subway/ chipotle style where you are able to customize everything you get. The staff here was super friendly and everything was fresh. trytheir house made lemonade

For a fast food restaurant, it is excellent!!! Everything is so fresh and deliciously made! My new go to place on Granville Street. You get to choose your own burrito or salad. They don t have gluten free tortilla however you can get a bowl.
I came here after a year to this place, changed alot in terms of food and service both. We met Aldo there, What a guy. We will be back for sure, and recommend everyone to come here and give a try!!

Fast and furious salad creation, with a million options and always fresh ingredients. Totally reasonably priced. Also a wonderful, lofty space, with lots of nooks and crannies to hide in if youre looking for a quiet place to eat your lunch. Also try their burritos! Theyre as large as an elephant, but much more tasty.
Such a cute little place with an amazing burger!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much, Kita. You are amazing!

reviews.review_text: Delicious food with great wholefood ingredients. Would recommend for a quick stop while walking around Granville. Alittle pricey for the add-ons but worth it. Food : 5/5
Lots of variety, fresh ingredients and large portions.  I will definitely go again.  The only downside is the location, very central but not clean.

Literally every time i come here i have a good time. Everything is reasonably priced! All the staff are super sweet and welcoming as well. Usually on some weekends theres a door man that lingers on the outside of the restaurant named Tim - Tim is most of the reason we even keep coming back! This guys energy is great, he is super sweet and gives great recommendations. Thanks Tim for your amazing services, even as a door man you make our experience a 10 everytime we see you! Thanks staff, big hugs xox
I ate here for the first time tonight and was really impressed with the quality of the food and cleanliness of the restaurant! Everything was fresh and tasted great. I ll be back again soon :)
Chicken Salad bowl was so good. One of those places that make you surprised when you enter from such a crowded place like Granville street into a cozy green corner like that.

Great prices for fresh and healthy ingredients, and large portions ! 6.5$ for a salad with two bases and 4 ingredients, add 2.3$ for some protein or premium ingredients, with really good dressings and large quantities. Im so glad I finally found a place that serves salads large enough for a big appetite !

Great location, soft ambiance and comfortable decor make for an enjoyable visit. Menu easy to navigate with a wide variety of eating restrictions, and preference for spicy/mild. I had the build your own burrito, which was delicious. No grease, fresh ingredients, clean tools and workspace, with compostable utensils and cups. House lemonade also awesome. Great service. Time of visit 4PM, Thurs
Reasonable price. delicious food. Similar to Subway with wider range of variations. Recommend for salad lovers

I had been craving churros for a very long time (years) but didnt know where to get them.  I was referred here by staff of another restaurant under the same owner.  I suspect the waitress thought there was a communication issue when I ordered only churros and a mojito as she called another fellow (owner or manager?) to assist her.  I hadnt tried tequila yet and mistakenly thought it was the liquor in mojitos.  The staff gently and patiently corrected me, redirecting me to a margarita instead. Churros were cooked perfectly: slightly crunchy yet still pleasantly soft.  They came with generous amounts of both creamy chocolate sauce and real whipping cream on the side, both of which had leftovers when I finished. Thankfully this location is a close walk from home so I will be returning again to sample some other menu choices - and maybe a mojito next time.
Welcoming and warm customer service. Salad is fresh, well assorted and very delicious. The best homemade gelato ever. Merci gracias thank you for the the fresh and healthy meal.
Great place for salads and custom healthy food made to order right in front of you!  Places little cramped but mostly we love their take out for the convenience and selection of healthy foods.
Delicious and filling burritos! Well worth the $12. Couldn t even finish it all in one sitting so it s lunch and supper.
Amazing service, great prices and you get lots of food for the meal.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi B Leva, thank you soooo much. We really appreciate your comments.

reviews.review_text: The bowls were amazing - healthy, full of flavour and lots of options. Have already been back.
When we went it wasn t busy, but the food was amazing and the waitress was super nice. Whenever I m back in Vancouver I m coming back for sure.
Wow, I enjoyed their salad! Fresh with plenty of choices. They got a nice atmosphere and awesome staff. Highly recommended.
Delicious tacos and service was amazing. We had chicken chipotle soup as well.
Burrito was fantastic, vibe is amazing. New gorgeous bar and renovations. Those leaving poor reviews because their favourite quick lunch spot has a new business model should be ashamed of themselves.
They should call it Satiated Guys cuz I left there positively satisfied.

Really healthy salads or a burrito packed full of fresh salad. Not stodgy at all. Cute place, great music and atmosphere. Staff were lovely. They make a surprisingly mean margarita. Well worth a visit!
Cheap sangrias for happy hour! Very attentive service
Amazing food! Very nice and very affordable!

Great burrito. Taco salad also a great choice. Came for a beer and to watch NFL game, got the happy hour special on the beer even though it was well past the HH hours. All around great hidden gem on Granville.

This place was great! Little gem in DT Vancouver. Very narrow. Vaulted ceilings, inviting decor. Super friendly staff and my (adult) kids and I gobbled up the fresh, yummy burritos and salad. Grab n Go or sit if theres room. Ill be back!

Fantastic option on a budget in Vancouver. Friendly staff. Fresh vegetables and great prices. The salads were great with chicken and avocado. The place is quite nice and its perfect for talk, work, share a coffee or just take a bite. Vegetarian options: Several vegan and vegetarian options

Truly a hidden gem in Vancouver. I would walk past this place every few days and never thought to check it out. One day I finally did and it was phenomenal. Their ingredients are some of the freshest I ve ever seen, and the bowls are a great portion size. If you re looking for a tasty, healthy lunch, this is the spot to go to.
Food is great along with the speed of service but pricey.

A-maz-ing!! In the city for an event and found this on Google maps and it did NOT disappoint. First off, such a chill vibe inside with the set up/decor and music playing. Secondly, their food is delicious. Like both my friend and I got build your own burritos and we knew from bite one that it was good. Also for one being sensitive to dairy, them having goat cheese on the menu, take all my money, because I will always say yes. Such a good spot for dinner, couldnt be more impressed
Great service, great Tacos, well put together drinks. A for sure check out spot when visiting Vancouver
Fantastic place! Maria is great. Highly recommend. Food
I had one of the best taco and Mexican bowl there. Services was good,but they forgot to substitue one thing i asked. And 2 things wasnt welcoming in there, it was loud music and it was cold.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Shell Me, thank you for the nice comments. Apologies for the music. It is much louder on the weekends nights.

reviews.review_text: That is nice owner u should come for a drink This nice place to chill
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for the nice review.

reviews.review_text: This place is so underrated! Fresh and good food, good quantity and fair price. I have been going there for the last 6 years and they always keep the same level of (fast and quality) service every time. If not better. Highly recommend.

First went here for a salad which was absolutely delicious, lots of choice of fresh ingredients all in front of you. Loved it so much I went back the next day and tried the tofu burrito which was equally as tasty! Staff are warming and helpful and the place is clean and nicely decorated. The first burrito of my life was here and I went again the next day to try a variant. Staff is nice and place feels clean. No reason to complain.
The bowls are just phenomenal. I get meals from here at least twice a week. 1 meal is usually enough for the entire day. Their coffee was amazing especially with oat milk.
Had the Mexican Chicken and Rice bowl. Amazing! Staff were super friendly! Great atmosphere   . Definitely going back!
Best burrito place ever!! Absolutely nothing bad to say! The ingredients were so fresh and flavourful, the serving size and proportions were perfect, and the staff was also very nice. Overall 10/10
Good food and cocktails, friendly service & free shots with tacos.
Their new renovation and menu is amazing! Tasty food and good atmosphere. They also make really good drinks! Perfect place to chill on Granville.
Good food & drinks

had no idea what I wanted or what the options were going in, but the staff were so patient and nice. The burrito was very good and for a can of coke it was pretty cheap. I would strongly recommend this for a quick lunch option, just be careful when you say you want a lot of hot sauce, they will give you a lot. definitely going back
Great service, great friendly staff! Amazing salad. for just under $10 I got an amazing salad that I built myself. I highly recommend the salad here.
The spicy chocolate chicken bowl is probably one of the best things I ve ever eaten, and I m not usually a fan of chicken.
Great avocado taco salad. Also impressed they do not prompt for tip at the machine. Great service.
Perfect for a dinner date!
delicious food! decent price! very good service. Customer reps are super patient and nice!

I still say this is one of the best lunch spots in all of Downtown. Perfect timing for a 30min lunch, and if you have a full hour its Fan Tastic. Whether you get a Burrito, Rice Bowl, Salad, or even sometimes theyll offer Soups or Mac&Cheese; its the ideal lunch. Their food doesnt seem to have any / many preservatives which is A-Mazing. Ive never seen them serve anything that wasnt 100% fresh; meaning its great for To Go as well. All in all, one of my favorite places to eat when Im downtown. :)

Oh my gosh. You seriously don t expect the salad to taste as good as it does!!! The yo so pretty salad was just fantastic. The miso sesame dressing was everything. My bf really enjoyed his taco salad and ended up using some of my dressing on it because it was just that good. Friendly service as well
We ordered the avocado taco salad and it was really delicious.

After coming from the gym sometimes Id come here with my buddies, and Ive gotta say... Its really good!!! I love the interior design as well and for me its one of the best burritos in the city. Its a great spot to have good cheap food, and chill upstairs with your buddies. I recommend coming here.
The tacos and margaritas were amazing! Decent portion sizes, definitely going to try the bowls next time
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Kiran. Thank you so much.

reviews.review_text: Delicious wholesome food. Accommodated take out. Thank you! It was so good.

I love this place! It is the healthiest option on Granville! It is a similar concept to Chipotle - except every thing is fresh and, as far as I can tell, made in house. There are many salad and bowl options in addition to burritos. The staff are friendly and efficient. I like sitting at the window and watching folks walk by on Granville. Top downtown casual option!
Great for a light lunch.
An interesting eatery which offers a choice between custom or a-la-carte salads... among other things. My Avocado Taco salad was well adorned with fresh ingredients and was almost a meal in itself.
Delicious salads made from premium fresh ingredients. One of the few places I ve found that offers olive oil instead of lesser oils.
We were hungry and wanted something quick and fresh and this hit the spot! Dietary restrictions: Gluten free Food : 5/5 |
They serve caipirinha

Fresh ingredients that you can taste the difference in. The burritos are really good! The guacamole is also worth adding, for once they actually add a significant amount for the extra charge. Id recommend this spot for anyone looking for a healthy place to eat.

This place is absolutely fantastic! Super fresh, super clean, and super sized portions at a killer price point. This is our go to lunch spot at the office and Ive even made the trip down with my better half. In my mind, a better version of Chipotle - and they have great salads too!

What an amazing location and people, we ordered 44 meals for our office and they were so kind they put staffs names. Very good portion, really tasty clean food. Thank you guys again you guys are the best :)
This place deserves more attention. The staff is welcoming. The food is great and served quickly. The interior is cozy.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much Pavlo. You re amazing.

reviews.review_text: I love this place. Plenty of delicious ingredients. Great for me because I have to be very cautious about what I eat. Very generous amount of salad for the price. I just wish they offered raw juice. Then I could just live there.
Vibes only, dope place in Vancouver hidden gem on Granville. Staff & the owner are super nice, food is dope & drinks are fantastic. Dont miss it.

Great healthy food! Fresh ingredients and inviting atmosphere. Portion sizes are small for the price. Could your staff be a little more generous with the toppings and ingredients.? Highly recommend this poor mans chipotle.!!

Tbh i had a very enjoyable first time experience today grabbing some take out while finishing up my stay in Vancouver.Loved the comfortable atmosphere, Quality service, and Awesome food matched with a variety of options.Whether its eating inside or to go Im sure it will be a positive experience.Keep up the good work guys!
